<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11957&amp;p=136700#p136700"><![CDATA[
Thanks for clarifying.<br /><br />Perhaps a good remix compo project might involve extracting the music (using <a href="https://nesdev.com/nt2re.zip" class="postlink">the format doc I made</a>) and converting it to something a more modern music engine can play, then doing a monster refactor of the game source itself to eliminate the cargo cult programming that was common in the pre-PowerPak days. Yes, I know it'll be a big job.<br /><br /><br /><strong>Wishlist</strong><br /><ul><li>Dump all music as instrument and pattern definitions </li><li>Get the title screen music playing in a modern NES music player (such as FamiTone, GGSound, or Pently), as a proof of concept </li><li>Get the rest of the music playing </li><li>Eliminate use of color $0D </li><li>Thorough code review, eliminating what have since been discovered as poor practices </li><li>Compress the nametables! </li><li>Add crosshair to visualize the velocity better </li><li>Add alternate polar control scheme to match more conventional <em>Scorched Earth</em>/<em>Gorillas</em> clones </li><li>Add a way to display the tongueman </li></ul><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Nov 20, 2014 4:30 pm</p><hr />
